 {"id": "bd-1kb", "title": "Expand canonical conformance fixture families for core semantic units", "description": "Current conformance suite has only 10 baseline fixtures with 0 Rust-comparable parity records. Need to expand fixture families to cover: region lifecycle corner cases (close under pending children, fast-path close), cancel propagation chains (severity strengthening, multi-child cancel), budget exhaustion rollbacks, channel FIFO fairness under pressure, timer ordering determinism. Target: 30+ fixture scenarios across CORE_SEMANTIC_FIXTURE_FAMILIES.md scope.", "status": "closed", "priority": 2, "issue_type": "task", "created_at": "2026-03-02T04:21:47.996767421Z", "created_by": "ubuntu", "updated_at": "2026-03-02T04:28:39.805337651Z", "closed_at": "2026-03-02T04:28:39.805307975Z", "close_reason": "Expanded conformance fixtures from 10 to 66 across 5 families (lifecycle, cancel, budget, channel, timer). Codec-equivalence: 33 pairs (up from 5). Profile-parity: 24 pairs (up from 2). All gates pass: conformance, codec-equivalence, profile-parity, unit tests, e2e.", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0, "labels": ["conformance", "fixtures", "testing"]}
